question: The "Dancing House" is located in which country?
explanation: Dancing House is located in the Czech Republic. It is also known as "Fred and Ginger". This building houses the office of Nationale-Nederlanden building. This building was designed by Vlada Milunic and Frank Gehry and was completed construction in 1996. The Dancing House has been called inappropriate among the baroque, Gothic and Art Nouveau buildings in the classical city of Prague.
